                            Peppo Card Grid
                        </div>
                    

                    

                    



                    <div id="page-content">
                        

<div class="unmargined" style="margin: 0 auto 20px; background-color: #b01; border: solid 1px #b01; border-radius: 20px; box-shadow: 0 1px 6px rgba(0,0,0,.25), inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,.8), inset 0 10px 1px rgba(255,255,255,.6), inset 0 -15px 30px rgba(0,0,0,.2); text-align: center; width: 500px;">
<div class="unmargined" style="margin: 20px 0; font-size: 300%; color: #fff; font-weight: bold; text-shadow: 1px 2px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.5);">
<p>ERMAHGERD STAHP</p>
</div>
<div class="unmargined" style="margin: 20px 0; color: #ff6;">
<p>This is a <em>template</em> page used internally by the SCP Wiki.</p>
</div>
<div class="unmargined" style="margin: 20px 0; font-size: 120%; font-weight: bold; color: #fff; text-shadow: 1px 2px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.25);">
<p>PLEASE DO NOT TOUCH THIS PAGE<br />
WITHOUT STAFF PERMISSION</p>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<h1 id="toc0"><span>What is this?</span></h1>
<p>This is a sortable, card-based display format primarily for author pages, but with the potential for other applications as well. For an example, see <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/dr-john-peppersghost-pepper-s-personnel-file">the creator's author page.</a></p>
<hr />
<h1 id="toc1"><span>Author</span></h1>
<p><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1553042); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1553042&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1599976289" alt="PeppersGhost" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1553042)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1553042); return false;">PeppersGhost</a></span></p>
<hr />
<h1 id="toc2"><span>Associated Templates</span></h1>
<p>I used as few pages as I could possibly accomplish this with. Due to technical limitations, I cannot include any content on these pages except what is integral to the functionality of the card grid.<br />
<a href="/component:peppo-card-base">peppo-card-base</a><br />
<a href="/component:peppo-card-structure">peppo-card-structure</a></p>
<hr />
<h1 id="toc3"><span>Setup instructions</span></h1>
<ul>
<li>Choose the page you want the to display the Card Grid on. For our purposes, we'll call this the <strong>Display Page</strong>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>First we need to add the CSS that will make the whole thing work. To do that, copy and paste the following code to your Display Page:</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include&#32;component:peppo-card-grid</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">|&#32;cardBG=&#32;changeThis</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">|&#32;color1&#32;=&#32;changeThis</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">|&#32;color2=&#32;changeThis</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">]]</span></p>
</blockquote>
<ul>
<li>Replace each &quot;changeThis&quot; with whatever color you want to use in your theme. For best results, use the hex code for the color you want. For example, if you want a color to be white, replace &quot;changeThis&quot; with &quot;#ffffff&quot;. <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/colors_picker.asp">This tool</a> will help you find a selection of hex codes.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Create a new page to store your cards on. We'll call this your <strong>Card Collection</strong>. You <strong>must</strong> have &quot;component:&quot; at the beginning of this page's URL. It will be tagged as a template.<br />
<br />
Example: <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/component:peppersghost-card-collection</span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Add the following code to your Card Collection:</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[div&#32;class=&quot;card-box&quot;]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
CARDS GO HERE<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[/div]]</span></p>
</blockquote>
<ul>
<li>Replace &quot;CARDS GO HERE&quot; with the peppo-card-base component below. We'll break down how each section works in just a sec.</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include&#32;component:peppo-card-base</span><br />
articleURL=your-source<br />
| {$orderNew} = -x<br />
| {$orderOld} = x<br />
| {$orderRate} = -xx<br />
| {$orderNum} = xxxxx<br />
| articleTitle = Your article's designation goes here<br />
| articleLink = <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">http://www.scp-wiki.net/your-url</span><br />
| articleName = Your article name goes here<br />
| articleQuote = Your quote goes here<br />
| articleImage = Your image URL goes here<br />
| hideCard = {$type} | hideCard = inherit<br />
| articleCredit = Co-author: Such-and-such<br />
| creditLink = <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/such-and-such</span><br />
| showCredit1 = inherit<br />
| articleCredit2 = Art by So-and-So<br />
| creditLink2 = <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/such-and-such</span><br />
| showCredit2 = inherit<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">]]</span></p>
</blockquote>
<ul>
<li>Check the collapsibles below for help customizing your card.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Source</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<h2 id="toc4"><span>Source</span></h2>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">articleURL=your-source</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Change &quot;your-source&quot; to the URL ending of the page you want the card to collection information from.</p>
<p>For example, let's say you want this card to represent the article <a href="/scp-2030">SCP-2030</a>. The URL for that scp is <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-2030">http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-2030</a>, so we'll replace &quot;your-source&quot; with &quot;scp-2030&quot;, like so:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">articleURL=scp-2030</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>NOTE:</strong> If you're testing your card grid on a sandbox, your source will need to be a local page on the sandbox site.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Order</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<h2 id="toc5"><span>Order</span></h2>
<blockquote>
<p>| {$orderNew} = -x<br />
| {$orderOld} = x<br />
| {$orderRate} = -xx<br />
| {$orderNum} = xxxxx</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is where the real magic happens. These values are what will determine how your cards are sorted.</p>
<p><strong>Be sure to leave the &quot;-&quot; in the orderNew and orderRate lines.</strong></p>
<p>To sort articles by Newest or Oldest, replace the &quot;x&quot; value for orderNew and orderOld with the chronological number of your article. For example, if it was your first article, we'd put &quot;1&quot;. If it's the 53rd article you wrote, we'd put &quot;53&quot;.</p>
<p>You can quickly find the chronological order you wrote your articles in by finding your author profile on SCPPER.com, then scrolling down to your article list and clicking &quot;Posted&quot; to change the order to ascending.</p>
<p>Next, replace &quot;xx&quot; with the rating of your article. You may be wondering why we don't use listpages to populate this section. Sadly, after hours of effort, I have not found a way to make that work, so we'll have to do it manually. Blame wikidot!</p>
<p>Finally, replace &quot;xxxxx&quot; to assign a custom sort number to your article. <strong>If your article is an SCP,</strong> this will be the SCP number. For example, if your card is for SCP-2030, you'll replace &quot;xxxxxx&quot; with &quot;202030&quot;.</p>
<p>Notice that extra &quot;20&quot; I included at the beginning? The extra 0 is to future-proof our code for Series 11. (It's going to happen someday!) The extra 2 at the front is just in case you decide you want to manually list tales and/or GoI articles before your SCPs.</p>
<p>Let's use SCP-2030 for our example code again. It's the 19th page I wrote for the wiki and its rating is currently at 1145, so my code will look like this:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>| {$orderNew} = -19<br />
| {$orderOld} = 19<br />
| {$orderRate} = -1145<br />
| {$orderNum} = 202030</p>
</blockquote>
<p>If you want another type of article to be listed before my SCPs, you'll want to change the first digit to either &quot;0&quot; or &quot;1&quot;. For example, if I wanted my tales to come first, I'd number them &quot;000001&quot;, &quot;000002&quot;, etc., and then number my GoI formats &quot;100001&quot;, &quot;100002&quot;, etc.</p>
<p>I'll explain how to use these values to set sorting preferences in the section called Creating Sorting Groups.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Title</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<h2 id="toc6"><span>Title</span></h2>
<blockquote>
<p>| articleTitle = Your article's designation goes here</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is what will be listed at the top of your card. My suggested use is as follows:</p>
<p><strong>If your card is for an SCP article,</strong> use the full SCP designation.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>| articleTitle = SCP-2030</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>If your card is for a tale,</strong> simply put &quot;Tale&quot;.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>| articleTitle = Tale</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>If your card is for a GoI format article,</strong> put the name of the GoI the format is for.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>| articleTitle = Parawatch</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Link,&nbsp;Name,&nbsp;and&nbsp;Quote</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<h2 id="toc7"><span>Link, Name, and Quote</span></h2>
<blockquote>
<p>| articleLink = <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">http://www.scp-wiki.net/your-url</span><br />
| articleName = Your article name goes here<br />
| articleQuote = Your quote goes here</p>
</blockquote>
<p>These three are very straightforward.</p>
<p>For articleLink, use the full URL of the page you want the card to link to.</p>
<p><strong>NOTE:</strong> Due to current issues with Chrome, it is suggested that you use &quot;scp-wiki.wikidot.com&quot; instead of &quot;scpwiki.com&quot; in your links.</p>
<p>For articleName, use the item's nickname or the title of your Tale.</p>
<p>For articleQuote, include a good line from the article. Alternatively, you could write a brief summary or description of the piece.</p>
<p>Using SCP-2030 as an example, this is what the code would look like:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>| articleLink = <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-2030</span><br />
| articleName = Laugh is Fun<br />
| articleQuote = Mrs. Carter smiles, the creature's tongue still extended down her throat.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Image</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<h2 id="toc8"><span>Image</span></h2>
<blockquote>
<p>| articleImage = Your image URL goes here</p>
</blockquote>
<p>First off: <strong>always</strong> source your images and make sure they're compatible with CC-BY-SA 3.0 licensing. <a href="/licensing-guide">Click here</a> for more info.</p>
<p>Including an image on your card is simple. Just replace &quot;Your image URL goes here&quot; with the direct link to the image you want to use. These should be hosted on-site, probably on your author page.</p>
<p>Example:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>| articleImage = <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/dr-john-peppersghost-pepper-s-personnel-file/1578.jpg</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>However,</strong> there may be cases where don't want to include an image on a card. When this happens, <strong>replace the entire line</strong> with the following code:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>| picTrue = null | picFalse = &#8212;]</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Don't sweat if that looks like gibberish. Just trust me on this one.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Type</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<h2 id="toc9"><span>Type</span></h2>
<blockquote>
<p>| hideCard = {$type} | hideCard = inherit</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is what will allow you to filter certain categories of cards. To use it, simply change &quot;type&quot; to whatever you want to name that category. Ignore everything else, and be sure to keep dollar sign and squiggly brackets.</p>
<p>Let's say I want my Display Page to have a tab that includes only tales, and also a tab that only includes GoI formats. To do this, I need three categories: {$scp}, {$tale}, and {$goi}. So on a card that's for an SCP article, my code will look like this:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>| hideCard = {$scp} | hideCard = inherit</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'll explain how to filter types in the section called Creating Sorting Groups.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Credit</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<h2 id="toc10"><span>Credit</span></h2>
<blockquote>
<p>| articleCredit = Co-author: Such-and-such<br />
| creditLink = <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/such-and-such</span><br />
| showCredit1 = inherit<br />
| articleCredit2 = Art by So-and-So<br />
| creditLink2 = <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/such-and-such</span><br />
| showCredit2 = inherit</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>First thing you should know:</strong> If you don't need to credit anyone on your card, you'll remove these lines entirely. If you only need to credit one person, you can remove the lines for articleCredit2, creditLink2, and showCredit2.</p>
<p>articleCredit and articleCredit2 are where you'll put whatever you want to be written on the credit lines at the bottom of the card.</p>
<p>creditLink and creditLink2 are the URLs you'll use to promote and/or source the people you're crediting.</p>
<p>showCredit1 and showCredit2 are only there to tell Wikidot to make the respective credit line visible. When one is removed, it hides the corresponding credit line.</p>
<p>As an example, let's say I'm going to make a card for <a href="/scp-001-ex">SCP-001-EX</a>. I'll want to credit my co-author, as well as the artist who made the image I'm using on my card. My code will look like this:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>| creditLink = <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/the-great-hippo">http://www.scp-wiki.net/the-great-hippo</a><br />
| showCredit1 = inherit<br />
| articleCredit2 = Art by Ionny_ani<br />
| creditLink2 = <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Ionny_ani/">https://www.reddit.com/user/Ionny_ani/</a><br />
| showCredit2 = inherit</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<ul>
<li>Copy the entire include again to add and customize another card. Repeat as many times as desired. <strong>Do not copy/paste the div code again.</strong> Make sure all your cards are sandwiched by the div code you added earlier!</li>
</ul>
<h1 id="toc11"><span>Creating Sorting Groups</span></h1>
<ul>
<li>Now comes the part where we bring it all together.<br />
<br />
First, create a tab module on your Display Page. The first tab you list will be your default sorting method.</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[tabview]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[tab&#32;Default&#32;Option]]</span><br />
Your first sorting group goes here<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[/tab]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[tab&#32;Alternate&#32;Option]]</span><br />
Your second sorting group goes here<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[/tab]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[/tabview]]</span></p>
</blockquote>
<ul>
<li>Paste the following into each spot where a sorting group will go:</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include&#32;component:card-collection</span><br />
| orderNew =<br />
| orderOld =<br />
| orderRate =<br />
| orderNum =<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">]]</span></p>
</blockquote>
<ul>
<li>Change &quot;card-collection&quot; to the end of the URL for your Card Collection.<br />
<br />
For example: If my Card Collection page's URL is &quot;<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/component:peppersghost-rules-everything</span>&quot;, then my first line will look like this:</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include:&#32;component:peppersghost-rules-everything</span></p>
</blockquote>
<ul>
<li>Choose a sorting type for that group:
<ul>
<li>orderNew displays the articles from newest to oldest.</li>
<li>orderOld displays them from oldest to newest.</li>
<li>orderRate displays the articles from highest rated to lowest.</li>
<li>orderNum displays articles by a manually entered numbered.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Type <strong>articleOrder</strong> after the equals sign next to your chosen sorting option. For all others, write <strong>null</strong>.<br />
<br />
Example:</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include&#32;component:peppersghost-rules-everything</span><br />
| orderNew = null<br />
| orderOld = null<br />
| orderRate = articleOrder<br />
| orderNum = null<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">]]</span></p>
</blockquote>
<ul>
<li>If you want a sorting group to filter cards by type, include the following code on a new line before the &quot;<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">]]</span>&quot; line:</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p>| typeName = none</p>
</blockquote>
<ul>
<li>This will hide any cards that have &quot;{$typeName}&quot; set as their &quot;hideCard&quot; value, so just change &quot;typeName&quot; to the name of the card type you want to hide. Repeat this step on a new line for every additional card type you want to hide.<br />
<br />
Let's say I have given all of my cards one of three hideCard values: {$scp}, {$tale}, and {$goi}. If I want to make a sorting group that only displays GoI format articles and lists them from oldest to newest, my code will look like this:</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include&#32;component:peppersghost-rules-everything</span><br />
| orderNew = null<br />
| orderOld = articleOrder<br />
| orderRate = null<br />
| orderNum = null<br />
| scp = none<br />
| tale = none<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">]]</span></p>
</blockquote>
<h1 id="toc12"><span>Wrapping up</span></h1>
<p>That's pretty much everything you need to know! Let's end with one final example.</p>
<p>Suppose that you want to make three sorting groups. The default option will list all cards by rating. The second will show only tales and GoI formats listed by rating. The third will list only tales from newest to oldest. The final code with all the different components together will look like this:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include&#32;component:peppo-card-grid</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">|&#32;cardBG=&#32;#333333</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">|&#32;color1&#32;=&#32;#b81818</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">|&#32;color2=&#32;#ffffff</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[tabview]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[tab&#32;Rating]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include&#32;component:peppersghost-rules-everything</span><br />
| orderNew = null<br />
| orderOld = null<br />
| orderRate = articleOrder<br />
| orderNum = null<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[/tab]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[tab&#32;No&#32;SCPs]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include&#32;component:peppersghost-rules-everything</span><br />
| orderNew = null<br />
| orderOld = null<br />
| orderRate = articleOrder<br />
| orderNum = null<br />
| scp = none<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[/tab]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[tab&#32;Tale&#32;Library]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include&#32;component:peppersghost-rules-everything</span><br />
| orderNew = null<br />
| orderOld = articleOrder<br />
| orderRate = null<br />
| orderNum = null<br />
| scp = none<br />
| goi = none<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[/tab]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[/tabview]]</span></p>
</blockquote>



